# Appendix AS — Temporal Inversion and the Configuration Zero-Baseline

### AS.1 — The Superluminal Phase Transition

Within the Scarlet framework, the invariant speed \(c\) characterizes the causal structure of the coarse-grained infrared (IR) manifold and emerges from the collective behavior of the microscopic space fabric. This causal structure remains valid only while the low-energy effective field theory (EFT) description remains applicable.

The EFT expansion parameter is defined by the ratio of the fundamental microscopic scale to the characteristic macroscopic curvature scale,

\[
\beta \equiv \frac{\ell_*}{L},
\]

where \(\ell_*\) denotes the ultraviolet (UV) cutoff length of the fabric and \(L\) represents the characteristic infrared scale of the system.

As the macroscopic scale approaches the microscopic resolution threshold, the system approaches the ultraviolet limit,

\[
\lim_{L\rightarrow\ell_*}\beta = 1.
\]

In this regime, the separation between ultraviolet and infrared degrees of freedom collapses. The coarse-grained metric description \(g_{\mu\nu}\) progressively loses completeness as a descriptor of geometric transport, while ultraviolet tetrad degrees of freedom become dynamically significant.

In this critical regime, the Levi-Civita sector,

\[
\left\{{}^{\lambda}{}_{\mu\nu}\right\},
\]

which ordinarily enforces smooth pseudo-Riemannian causality, becomes subordinate to the underlying Weitzenböck connection determined by the ultraviolet tetrad fields \(e^a{}_\mu\),

\[
\Gamma^{(W)\lambda}{}_{\mu\nu}
=
e^\lambda{}_a\,\partial_\nu e^a{}_\mu.
\]

The fabric therefore transitions into a highly local phase dominated by ultraviolet tetrad fields and strongly non-linear torsional dynamics. Geometric information is carried primarily through microscopic fabric alignment rather than through smooth metric propagation. Consequently, the emergent causal structure associated with \(c\) no longer constitutes the appropriate macroscopic descriptor. Within Scarlet, the term *superluminal* refers to propagation that exceeds the validity domain of the emergent infrared velocity bound and should not be interpreted as transport relative to an intact pseudo-Riemannian light cone.

