The interval \(t_*\) is interpreted as an invariant ordering scale of the microscopic fabric rather than as a globally synchronized coordinate clock.

The Master Clock is identified with the directional relaxation of ultraviolet tetrad fluctuations toward a common configuration-space attractor, referred to as the **mutual center**. This process establishes a structural measuring point of zero—a configuration-space baseline against which all emergent temporal relations are defined.

At this zero-baseline, macroscopic temporal ordering, metric distance, and the infrared notion of causality emerge through coarse-graining and renormalization-group flow from the underlying microscopic dynamics.

Although an observer may alter their state of motion and invert local wavefront reconstruction relations, they remain embedded within the microscopic relaxation process of the fabric itself. The ultraviolet tetrad degrees of freedom continue to evolve according to the invariant interval \(t_*\), which persists as the fundamental ordering scale underlying all emergent relativistic phenomena.

