As the characteristic scale of the system approaches the ultraviolet cutoff,

\[
L\rightarrow\ell_*,
\]

the low-energy effective field description ceases to be sufficient and the dynamics must be described by the complete Riemann-Cartan action.

Within Scarlet it is assumed that the quadratic torsional contribution scales more rapidly than the infrared curvature sector as

\[
\beta\rightarrow1.
\]

Accordingly, the Einstein tensor \(G_{\mu\nu}\), which governs smooth infrared geometry, becomes subordinate to the quadratic torsional sector \(\Theta_{\mu\nu}\), such that

\[
