+
\frac{\alpha}{\ell_*^2}
\Theta_{\mu\nu}
\right)
\propto
\Theta_{\mu\nu},
\]

where \(\alpha\) is a dimensionless coupling parameter.

The ordinary light-cone structure defined by the metric tensor \(g_{\mu\nu}\) therefore loses its role as the primary mediator of causal transport. Propagation no longer proceeds through continuous null geodesics of a smooth four-dimensional manifold. Instead, interactions become governed by non-local geometric transport encoded by the absolute parallelism of the Weitzenböck connection,

\[
\Gamma^{(W)\lambda}{}_{\mu\nu}
=
e^\lambda{}_a
\partial_\nu e^a{}_\mu.
\]

Causal ordering is therefore transferred from metric propagation to the sequential relaxation of the microscopic fabric itself.

